cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.CL 

This paper presents an algorithm for learning to aggregate the predictions of an ensemble of binary classifiers, which is a common problem in machine learning. The algorithm is scalable and does not require assumptions on the structure or origin of the ensemble, making it applicable to a wide range of scenarios. Given these characteristics, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
